Tomorrow's Wordle

January 24, 2022 · 62 min · Peter Boone  · Source

I have been playing wordle recently (like a lot of people). I decided to check out how Josh gets the wordle of the day, so I inspected the source. Turns out, it’s all done client-side based on todays date!

So a little bit of copy/paste and we can get the wordle for tomorrow!

function calculateIndex(todaysDate, startDate) { 
  var s = new Date(todaysDate); 
  t = new Date(startDate).setHours(0, 0, 0, 0) - s.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0); 
  return Math.round(t / 864e5);
} 

function getSolution(date) { 
  var a, s = getIndex(date); 
  return a = s % potentialWords.length, potentialWords[a]
} 
function getIndex(date) { 
  return calculateIndex(START_DATE, date) 
}
